                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section VIII.	In case the BUYER requests for disinterment, the following requirements shall apply:
                        </p>
                        
                        <p style="font-size: 10px; margin-left: 30px" >
                            <strong style="font-weight: bold;font-size: 10px"> A.</strong>     If the BUYER requests an interred body or bones or urn to be transferred to any lot/crypt within the Memorial Park and the BUYER’s 
                            lot/crypt contains an interred body or bone/urn sets, a disinterment fee and re-interment fee shall be charged. However, disinterment
                            of interred body will only be allowed provided same was interred at least 5 years and the necessary local and national health requirements 
                            are submitted prior to disinterment. The request for dis-interment shall be submitted to the office and dis-interment fee and re-interment
                            fee shall be settled at least seven (7) calendar days ahead of actual dis-interment. The disinterred body or bone/urn sets will be re-interred 
                            to the new lot/crypt on the same date of disinterment in the presence of the BUYER.  However, in cases where the body that has been disinterred
                            is not in the acceptable decomposition state, the SELLER has the right to discontinue the disinterment.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px; margin-left: 30px" >
                            <strong style="font-weight: bold;font-size: 10px"> B.</strong>     If the BUYER wishes to transfer an interred body or bones or urn to another Memorial Park and
                            the BUYER’s lot/crypt contains an interred body or bone/urn sets, a dis-interment fee and re-interment bond is charged. However, disinterment of interred body will
                            only be allowed provided the same was interred at least 5 years and the necessary local and national health requirements are submitted prior to disinterment.
                            The request for disinterment shall be submitted to the office and dis-interment fee and re-interment bond shall be settled at least seven (7) calendar days ahead 
                            of actual disinterment. The disinterred body or bone/urn sets should be claimed by the BUYER from the SELLER on the same date of disinterment. Subsequently, 
                            the re-interment bond will be refunded.  Otherwise, the SELLER would reinter the disinterred body on the following day, in which case the re-interment bond will be forfeited.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px; margin-left: 30px" >
                            <strong style="font-weight: bold;font-size: 10px"> C.</strong>  Should there be a request for dis-interment by virtue of a court order, dis-interment will be
                            allowed and the corresponding dis-interment and re-interment fee shall be charged to the BUYER and has to be settled within twenty four (24) hours from the
                            date the court order is received. Should there be late payments, the amount due shall be subject to a penalty, computed from the date the delay occurs. 
                            In failure to pay the said amount within thirty (30) calendar days, the SELLER is constrained to file a case against the BUYER for the collection of the sum of money.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section IX.	In the event that the memorial park of the SELLER is subject to real property tax or any special assessments, the BUYER shall pay the SELLER promptly an amount equal to the real estate tax or special assessment allocable to the above-described lots / crypts. On default of the BUYER of said payments, SELLER has the option to advance the necessary amount therefore, if it so desires, and the BUYER is obligated to reimburse the SELLER of said amount upon demand, plus an interest thereon of 24% per annum computed from date of SELLER’s disbursement until fully paid. Real property tax shall be paid by the BUYER starting from the year his account (lot/crypt) has been fully paid. Any and all taxes or expenses due and payable on account of this AGREEMENT or on account of any subsequent document transferring the ownership of the property to the BUYER shall be borne by the BUYER.

                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section X.	Markers of any kind, conforming to the rules and regulations of the SELLER will be permitted to mark interments in the above-described property.  All materials to be used for the construction of niches or mausoleums must be of permanent qualities such as marble, granite or bronze. Painted finish marker, niches or mausoleums are not allowed. The BUYER may also erect upon said property a memorial in the form of a monument statue, vault, catafalque or mausoleum, subject, however, to the rules and regulations of the park.  An exception to the current rules and regulations now existing, or which hereafter may be adopted or amended, governing the size, placement, design and construction details of such memorials, shall be attached hereto upon effectivity of such event.

                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XI.	The BUYER recognizes the significance of continued and uninterrupted contact with the SELLER and accepts the fact that it is his duty to notify the SELLER promptly in writing of any change in his mailing address and/or new contact address to maintain quality service.  It is hereby agreed that the mere sending of SELLER’S letters, notices, reminders, statements, communications, demands, summons, notices or orders of the Court, or papers of whatever kind or nature to the BUYER at the address indicated on this contract or any address subsequently submitted in writing by the BUYER to the SELLER, either by personal service or by registered mail, shall constitute proper, valid and effective service for all legal intents and purposes.  The fact that the BUYER did not actually receive such letter, notice, orders, summons, or communications or the same has been returned unclaimed or that no person found at said address, or said address is fictitious or cannot be located, or BUYER moved to another address without notifying the SELLER, shall not excuse nor relieve the BUYER from the effect of such letter, notice, orders, summons or communications.

                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XII.	The amount transacted thru any national or international establishment, facility or institution shall not affect in any circumstance or situation the net receivable by the SELLER (devaluation/ depreciation or appreciation in the purchasing power of the Philippine Peso) for any reason whatsoever during the term of this agreement. The net amount as above mentioned pertains to actual payment, interest and penalty, if applicable.

                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XIII.	The BUYER is bound to obey and comply with all lawful directions, issuances, and Company Rules and Regulations issued or which may be issued by the SELLER and shall at all times promote the interests of the SELLER to the best of his ability and shall not do anything which may cause or tend to cause any loss, prejudice or damage to the SELLER
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XIV.  The company reserves the right to amend existing provisions and to impose and/or amend charges and/or other fees which deemed necessary at any time during the contract period.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XV.	 If upon default by the BUYER, the SELLER shall engage the services of counsel for collection, lot/crypt repossession, or for litigation, the BUYER agrees to pay to the SELLER attorney’s fees including all interest and service charges, as well as the expenses which fee shall not be less than  25% of the total obligation.  The PARTIES hereby agree that the exclusive venue of all suits to enforce this Agreement shall be in the proper courts of Muntinlupa or Sta. Rosa.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XVI.  BUYER manifests that prior to the signing of this agreement he has inspected and verified the status of subject Memorial Garden or Bone Crypt Establishment. 
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XVII.  The BUYER represents with his signature the acceptance of the terms and conditions of this agreement and has been carefully read by him or has been read to him and/or explained to him in a language or dialect known to him, and that he understands its terms and conditions, and that there are no covenants, conditions, warranties or representations other than those contained herein.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XVIII. Upon full payment the SELLER shall issue the CERTIFICATE OF OWNERSHIP to the above stated name as the registered owner of the specific lot/crypt.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XIX. The terms and conditions hereof shall extend to and bind the heirs, executors, administrators, assigns and successors in interest of the respective parties hereto.  The BUYER, his heirs, successors, and assigns shall have hold and use the property subject to the rules and regulations of the SELLER for the government of the Memorial Park now enforce and those which may hereafter be adopted; that a copy of said rules and regulations and all amendments, additions and modifications thereto is kept in the SELLER’s office and is subject to inspection by the BUYER at all times during normal office hours, said rules and regulations and all amendments, additions and modifications thereto are hereby incorporated herein and made integral parts hereof by reference as it set forth herein in full.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                           Section XX.  Separability Clause.  In the event that any of the provisions of the latter is declared unconstitutional, the validity of the other provisions shall not be affected by such declaration.
 
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size: 10px"> 
                            Section XXI.  Effectivity.  The above mentioned terms and conditions shall take effect upon authentication of this document by the authorized signatories of SELLER and BUYER. 
                        </p>
